{F:1}{topic:How To Use} The {Picture:i,cvlogo} Software{F:0}{Rule:0}{Picture:R,Logo}
{Picture:i,cvlogo} is a document reader for hyper-linked documents. You can read the text in this window using the scroll bar to the right and the tools in the toolbox at the top of the window. If you do not know how to use the scroll bar, please use your RISC OS user guide to become more familiar with RISC OS before proceeding.

Text presented using {Picture:i,cvlogo} may be read in the normal way (ie from start to finish) as you might expect. The concept of hyper-linking extends this to allow the text to be read in a way more compatible with the way you think.

{Index:Cross References}A hyper-link is a cross reference to another point in the text where there is further relevant information. These cross references are indicated in the text by underlined words and you may click on any such words to follow the cross references. Try this now by clicking {Ref:here,Trial Point}.

Notice that whenever the pointer is over a cross reference it changes to a symbol like this: {Picture:I,pointer}. This serves as an extra reminder and also helps identify the exact area where you may click to follow a cross reference.

As well as following cross references you may use the {Ref:toolbox,Toolbox Commands} and the program {Ref:menu,Main Menu} to help with reading the text.

You may change the size of the window to make more text visible. If you change the width, the text will be reformatted appropriately. There is a minimum limit to the width of each document, generally relating to the size of pictures used.

{Picture:L,File}{Index:Loading}New {picture:i,cvlogo} document files may be loaded by dragging them onto the application or by double clicking them. Note that only one document may be loaded at a time but you may run several copies of the software simultaneously if you really need to view two documents at once. You can recognise {picture:i,cvlogo} document files by their icons which look like the illustration on the left  (If you use small icons in your filer windows, they will look like this: {Picture:I,smallfile}). {Index:Creating Documents}If you have a {Ref:type A (advanced) version,Versions} of this software, you may drag text files to the application to compile and load them.

Your use of this software is governed by the terms of the {Ref:licence,Licences} under which you are using it. Please be sure that you are complying with the terms of the licence before proceeding.
{Rule:1}
