{F:00000000000001
{topic:Applications}{F:0}{Rule:0}{Picture:R,Logo}
{picture:i,cvlogo} is a versatile medium for presenting information of all sorts to readers of all levels of ability. The software was primarily designed for the presentation of curriculum material in educational environments but is equally useful in other areas, eg on-line manuals such as this.

You may present your own information if you have a {Ref:type A (advanced) version,Versions} of the software which includes a compiler for your own documents. You may also be able to make use of the growing range of ready made {picture:i,cvlogo} documents which are available. These include information on subjects ranging from the history of science to Shakespeare plays with cross-referenced glossaries and plot overviews. Remember that the printing facilities of {picture:i,cvlogo} extend these into a useful paper based resource as well as a computer resource.

Different versions of {picture:i,cvlogo}, and a wide selection of {picture:i,cvlogo} documents, are available from a wide variety of sources. In case of difficulty, please {Index:Contact}contact:{f:2}

